abstract: Trans-Pacific Partnership trade pact shakes up impending Canadian national election; has produced vociferous debate concerning agreement's impact on auto industry.
lead_paragraph: The debate on whether the Trans-Pacific Partnership trade pact benefits or damages the economy isn’t the only issue in a heated election campaign in Canada. But it could tip the balance in a close three-way contest.

headline.main: Pacific Trade Deal Jolts Canadian Campaign
